    "justification": null,
    "gallery_text": null,
    "label_text": "Functioning like a small poster, a book cover must quickly capture a viewer\u2019s attention and provoke curiosity about the content within, contributing an enduring element to the reader\u2019s experience. The covers designed by Alvin Lustig in the 1940s and 1950s employ abstracted iconography and simple typography and lettering to create emotionally compelling representations of a book\u2019s themes. Lustig, who died at 40, is remembered as one of America\u2019s greatest modern designers.",
